he could to promote the cause of religious unity. In On Mending the Peace of the Church he urged rulers to enact moderate reforms that would satisfy all parties and avoid confessional division. When Martin Luther responded to this attempt at a "middle path" between "truth and error" in his Letter Concerning Erasmus of Rotterdam (1534), denouncing Erasmus as a skeptic and not a Christian, Erasmus responded indignantly with his Purgation against the Slanderous Letter of Luther. Erasmus’ only other work published in this period turned out to be one of his most popular, On Preparing for Death.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aChristian.  aChurch.  aCollected Works of Erasmus.  aDesiderius Erasmus.  aErasmus.  aGermany.  aLuther.  aNetherlands.  aQueen Mary.  aRenaissance history.  aRotterdam.  adeath.  aearly modern history.  aphilosophy.  areligious civil war.1 aEstes, James M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMiller, Clarence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831106904530 cprintz978148750585140uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753283340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487532833423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487532833/original  a978-3-11-069045-3  Universi